Source: CNN [edited]

Anthrax, post office contamination - USA (DC): possible
-------------------------------------------------------
WASHINGTON DC: The US Postal Service on Thursday closed 11 post offices in
the Washington area as it tested a Navy postal facility that handles mail
for government agencies for possible anthrax contamination. "The safety of
our employees and customers is the Postal Service's highest priority," said
Postal Service vice president Azeezaly Jaffer. Therefore, out of an
abundance of caution, the Postal Service has decided to close and test
facilities for biohazard contamination."
A spokeswoman for the Department of Homeland Security said on-site testing
and other preliminary tests came back positive for anthrax at the Navy
facility, and further testing is being done. The detection of the
potentially deadly pathogen came on Wednesday, the spokeswoman said, and
officials are "exploring" whether any precautionary measures need to be
taken for the workers at the Navy Consolidated Mail Facility, located at
the Naval District Washington Anacostia Annex.
All mail is irradiated before it gets to the facility so that there is very
little risk of potential exposure. No one has been hospitalized in the
incident, a Navy spokesman said, but the facility has been closed. "Most of
this mail moving through the Navy's facility was processed through the
Postal Service's V Street facility that processes government mail," Jaffer
said. "The contractor that transported this mail also collected mail from
other Washington DC area facilities."
In addition to the V Street facility, the Postal Service closed 10 post
offices in Washington, Maryland and Virginia. The Navy spokesman said the
level of anthrax detected by the automatic equipment at the Navy facility
was well below infectious levels, in the range of 100 to 140 spores.
Infectious levels begin at about 10 000 spores. The spokesman said a
follow-up test also came back positive for non-infectious levels of anthrax.
Authorities from the FBI, the Naval Criminal Investigative Services and
postal inspectors are investigating the discovery. List of closed post
offices:
* V Street Facility, 300 V Street NE, Washington DC 20098-9998
* Southwest Post Office, 45 L Street SW, Washington DC 20024-9998
* Ward Place Post Office, 2121 Ward Place NW, Washington DC 20037-9998
* Friendship Station Post Office, 4005 Wisconsin Avenue NW, Washington DC
20016-9998
* U.S. Post Office Andrews AFB, 1668 D Street, Andrews AFB MD 20762-9998
* U.S. Post Office Silver Spring, 8616 2nd Avenue, Silver Spring MD 20910-9998
* Calvert Distribution Center, 6511 Baltimore Avenue, West Hyattsville MD
20783-9998
* Westlake Post Office, 10421 Motor City Drive, Bethesda MD 20817-9998
* South Station Post Office, 1210 South Glebe Road, Arlington VA 22204-9998
* Eads Street Station, 1720 S Eads Street, Arlington VA 22202-9998
* Buckingham Station, 235 N Glebe Road, Arlington VA 22203-9998
(byline: Jamie McIntyre and Kevin Bohn)
